        <div id="Symp"><h3>Symptoms</h3>

        

        <p>

            There are many different symptoms that a cancer can cause but they may also be caused by other problems. If the symptoms last for a couple of weeks, it is very important to see a doctor to get diagnosed and treated. Sometimes we do not get things so serious until we feel the pain, but it is very important to know that ‘early cancer does not cause pain’. So if you have the below symptoms, do not wait to see a doctor until you feel the pain.
            </p>

            <p>

            You will get a thickening skin and a cough that does not go away, painful urination, problems with eating such as changes in appetite, discomfort after eating and swallowing difficulties. Also weight gaining or weight loss without knowing the reasons, abdominal pain, and night sweats, unusual bleeding, blood in the urine, vaginal bleeding and feeling week or very tired. 
            </p>

            <p>

            Instead of these symptoms, breast cancers will get the changes like change in size or shape of the breast or nipple and change in texture of breast skin.
            </p>

