        <div id="Reme"><h3>Remedies</h3>

        <br>

            
        <p>There are many cancer treatments and the type of the treatment is based on the type of cancer and how advanced it is.
        The main types of cancer treatment include:
        </p>

        <li>Surgery</li>
        <p>
        It is the procedure in which the surgeons remove the cancer from the body. Small, thin knives and sharp tools are used to cut the body and do cuts through skin, muscles and sometimes through bones. Surgery is used to remove the tumor, debulk a tumor (part of a tumor is removed as it is dangerous to remove the whole tumor), ease cancer symptoms (remove tumors that are causing pain)
        </p>

        <li>Radiation therapy</li>
        <p>
        In radiation therapy, high doses of radiation are used to kill cancer cells and shrink tumors. There are two types of radiation therapy “external beam and internal”. Radiation therapy is used either to treat the cancer or ease cancer symptoms. </p>

        <li>Chemotherapy</li>
        <p>
        In chemotherapy drugs are used to kill the cancer cells. It works by stopping or slowing the growth of cancer cells which grow and divide so quickly. This is also used either to treat the cancer or ease cancer symptoms. </p>

        <li>Immunotherapy</li>
        <p>
        It is a type of a cancer treatment that helps the immune system fight cancer as it is the system in our body to fight infections and other diseases. It is made up of white blood cells, organs and tissues of the lymph system. Immunotherapy is type of biological therapy. Biological therapy is a type of treatment that uses substances made from living organism to treat cancer.</p>

        <li>Targeted therapy</li>
        <li> Hormone therapy</li>
        <li> stem cell transplant</li>
        <li> precision medicine </li>

        <p>
These are the other treatment types for cancers.</p>


